{{Infobox Government agency |logo = Emblem_of_Iran.svg |logo_width = 50px |nativename = وزارت علوم، تحقیقات و فناوری |ministry_name = Ministry of Science, Research and Technology of I.R.IRAN |picture = |picture_width = 300px |picture_caption = View of the Ministry of Science, Research and Technology Central Building |formed = 2000 |preceding1 = Ministry of Culture and Higher Education |jurisdiction = [[Islamic Republic of Iran]] |minister1_name = [[Mansour Gholami]] |website = http://www.msrt.ir }} {{Politics of Iran}} The '''Ministry of Science, Research and Technology''' ('''MSRT''') is the [[government ministry]] of [[science]], [[research]] and [[technology]] in the [[Islamic Republic of Iran]]. State-run (non-medical) [[List of Iranian Universities|universities of Iran]] are under the direct supervision of Iran's Ministry of Science, Research and Technology. The ministry was established in 2000 when the ministry of culture and higher education was renamed as the ministry of science, research and technology.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Abdol S. Soofi|author2=Sepehr Ghazinoory|title=Science and Innovations in Iran: Development, Progress, and Challenges|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_C5EZ7SlCm0C&pg=PA66|accessdate=26 July 2015|date=22 January 2013|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-03009-2|page=66}}</ref>
In 2000 the ministry set up the Aerospace Research Institute.<ref>{{cite book|author=Parviz Tarikhi|title=The Iranian Space Endeavor: Ambitions and Reality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1VQlBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA60|accessdate=26 July 2015|date=19 July 2014|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-3-319-05347-9|page=60}}</ref>
